<item>
            <title>[LU-4661] Some issues of finding target in LMV</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4661</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With DNE every object can have two locks in different namespaces:&lt;br/&gt;
lookup lock in space of MDT storing direntry and update/open lock&lt;br/&gt;
in space of MDT storing inode. In lmv_find_cbdata/lmv_lock_lock,&lt;br/&gt;
it should try the MDT that the FID maps to first, since this can&lt;br/&gt;
be easily found, and only try others if that fails.&lt;br/&gt;
In the error handler of lmv_add_targets, it should check whether&lt;br/&gt;
ld_tgt_count is being increased before ld_tgt_count is being -1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/8019/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/8019/&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will update the patch later.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
